<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,152,294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="558">
Wing. Section of M between dm-Cu and bend of M 3.6 times as long as section between dm-Cu and r-m. Membrane largely brownish with a whitish spot posterodistally (
<figureCitation box="[907,994,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-208@5.[151,1436,661,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Melanophora spp. 9–10. Wing of Melanophora chia sp. nov. 9. ♂, holotype. 10. ♀, paratype. 11–12. Epandrial complex in posterior view. 11. Melanophora chia sp. nov. (♂, paratype), scale bar: 0.1 mm. 12. Melanophora roralis (Linnaeus) (♂, Sardinia), scale bar: 0.2 mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="558">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
